ut.cshtml"; }  &lt;div class="navbar navbar-default navbar-fixed-top"&gt;    &lt;div class="container"&gt;         &lt;div class="navbar-header"&gt;             &lt;button type="button" class="navbar-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-target=".navbar-collapse"&gt;                 &lt;span class="icon-bar fa fa-user fa-3x"&gt;tester&lt;/span&gt;                 &lt;span class="icon-bar"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;                 &lt;span class="icon-bar"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;             &lt;/button&gt;             &lt;button class="navbar-brand" id="editUser"&gt;Edit&lt;/button&gt;             &lt;button class="navbar-brand" id="addUser"&gt;Add User&lt;/button&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;          &lt;div class="navbar-collapse collapse"&gt;             &lt;ul class="nav navbar-nav navbar-right"&gt;                 &lt;li id="settings-menu" class="dropdown"&gt;                     &lt;a href="#" id="drop4" role="button" class="dropdown-toggle" data-toggle="dropdown"&gt;&lt;i class="fa fa-user fa-3x"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;                     &lt;ul class="dropdown-menu" role="menu" aria-labelledby="drop4"&gt;                     &lt;/ul&gt;                 &lt;/li&gt;             &lt;/ul&gt;          &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="container"&gt;     &lt;div&gt;         @RenderBody()     &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;hr&gt; &lt;/div&gt; @RenderSection("Scripts", required: false) @Scripts.Render("~/MyBundle") </code></pre>  <p>This page is supposed to use the _UserLayout page. However, I had to add the <code>@Scripts.Render("~/MyBundle")</code> to the page. </p>  <pre><code>@{     ViewBag.Title = "List";     Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_UserLayout.cshtml"; }  &lt;h2&gt;User View&lt;/h2&gt;  @Scripts.Render("~/MyBundle")  &lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;     $('#editUser').on('click', function () {         alert('test');     }); &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Am I doing something wrong here? Why did I have to add <code>@Scripts.Render("~/MyBundle")</code> to th